<HEADLINE>
FT  08 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Morris Ashby rises to Pounds 839,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
On turnover up 42 per cent from Pounds 8.13m to Pounds 11.6m in the six
months to September 30, Morris Ashby, the USM-quoted diecasting and
machining group, reported pre-tax profits of Pounds 839,000, an increase of
31 per cent on the previous Pounds 639,000.
Mr Norman Gardner, chairman, said: 'Overall, only one of our top 20
customers placed less business with us.'
He added that the long term future looked healthy with a strong forward
order book, but some customers were showing less confidence than had been
expected.
Earnings per share were 6.3p (5.5p) and the interim dividend is raised to 2p
(1.7p).
</TEXT>
