FT  08 DEC 93 / UK Company News: BIL Securities sells stake in Caffyns
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Caffyns, the Sussex-based motor dealer, yesterday announced that BIL
Securities (Far East), the New Zealand investment company owned by Sir Ron
Brierley, had disposed of its 23.6 per cent stake in the company.
The disposal by the company, a wholly owned subsidiary of BIL (Far East
Holdings), follows the sale of other stakes earlier this year in Guinness
Peat Group and Budgens, the food retailing chain.
The group's holding in Caffyns comprised 1.18m ordinary 50p shares and two
tranches of preference shares.
Caffyns shares rose 10p to close at 388p on the news.
