<HEADLINE>
FT  08 DEC 93 / Bemrose buys US calendar publisher for Dollars 27m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
1. Bemrose to buy:
Bemrose Corp., the Derby security and promotional printer, is to pay Dollars
27m (Pounds 17.9m) cash for McCleery-Cumming, the second largest US
publisher of advertising calendars.
2. Playboy to religion:
Styles range from religous subjects, scenic wildlife and American art to
'Playboy' glamour calendars.
3. Geo. Washington bedrock:
Two-thirds of sales are generated from the 'George Washington' range of
calendars sold through more than 3,000 independent US distributors.
4. Blue chip:
The balance of sales are customer-specific designs produced for large
commercial customers like Ford, General Motors, John Deer, Wal-Mart and
Texaco.
5. Selling out:
Four of McCleary-Cumming's management team own the majority of the company's
shares. Selling to Bemrose, they will retire as multi-millionaires. 'Quote
to come: we only did it for the grandchildren'.
6. Printing profits:
It posted pre-tax profits of Dollars 5.05m in the year to February, up from
Dollars 4.45m a year earlier, on sales of Dollars 31.8m (Dollars 32.5m.) Net
assets at the end of February were Dollars 8.49m.
7. 90 years young:
The McCleery-Cumming calendar business started in 1903 and expanded by
buiyng the calendar division of Newman Rudolf of Chicago in 1944.
8. A chunk of 'Hawkeye' state on the Skunk
The company, which employs up to 350 people including 200 staff who work
seasonally. It has a 20-acre site on the Skunk River in Washington, Iowa.
9. Shareholders tapped:
Bemrose will fund the deal with a 1-for-4 rights issue at 325p per share,
underwritten by SG Warburg, to raise a net Pounds 19.5m. The shares closed
up xp at 3xxp yesterday.
10. Bemrose booms:
Bemrose forecasts pre-tax profits, before exceptional credits, of at least
Pounds 10m (Pounds 6.25m) in the year to January 1, for earnings per share
of 27.90p (22.18p).
11. 'Excellent fit':
Mr Roger Booth, Bemrose's chief executive, said the acquisition was 'an
outstanding opportunity'. Bemrose, already number three in the US market,
moves a whisker shy of number one slot. The deal will ehance earnings in
1994.
12. Make-up-your-mind time:
The deal is subject to shareholder approval at an extraodinary meeting on
December 23.
</TEXT>
