FT  08 DEC 93 / Brighter economic outlook indicated
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Another rise in the Central Statistical Office's shorter leading index of
economic activity points to a favourable outlook for the economy.
The index, which is supposed to indicate economic turning points in activity
about five months in advance, was buoyed by increases in share prices and
new-car registrations.
There has been a slow-down in the fall of the longer leading index,
reflecting increases in housebuilding starts in recent months. The
coincident index, which tracks the business cycle, has maintained steady
increases since the second quarter of last year.
