FT  08 DEC 93 / Plea on divorce pact rejected
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A divorced father who is being asked for extra money by the Child Support
Agency failed yesterday to overturn a 'clean break' divorce settlement under
which he gave up his share of the family home on the understanding that he
would not pay maintenance.
Mr Gary Crozier, of Gretna Green, Dumfriesshire, had asked the High Court to
set aside the divorce settlement and give him his share from the sale of the
home.
Mrs Justice Booth said the settlement contained provision for nominal
maintenance of 5p a year. This reflected the legal principle that the clean
break formula had never applied to the on-going responsibility of parents to
a child.
