FT  07 DEC 93 / Ukraine halts all bank loans
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KIEV
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Ukraine government and central bank have banned bank loans until January
to fight hyperinflation, but bankers have said the move could ruin the
banking system, Reuter reports from Kiev.
A joint statement from the government and central bank said the ban, which
took effect late last week, affected both central bank affiliates and
commercial banks.
'Issuing loans in Ukraine is banned until the end of the year because of the
country's very difficult financial situation. Bankers who violate the new
rules could face criminal charges,' the statement said. It gave no details.
Leading Ukrainian bankers condemned the decision and accused the government
and central bank of trying to take control of commercial banks.
The move follows the government's suspension of transactions on Ukraine's
sole currency exchange last month in an attempt to contain the collapse of
the financial system.
</TEXT>
