FT  07 DEC 93 / World News in Brief: Child agency blamed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A divorced Nottinghamshire man who earned Pounds 500 a month was found
hanged the day after the Child Support Agency tripled his monthly
maintenance payment to Pounds 300. Pieces of paper with calculations were
found scattered under Graham Clay's body. His family blamed the tragedy
directly on the agency. Backing for review of child support, Page 10
