FT  07 DEC 93 / Observer: Sleep tight
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The British Association of Hotel Accountants has spent two years drawing up
new guidelines for surveyors who have to value hotels - it is to be hoped -
accurately. But will it do any good?
The BAHA committee which drew up the guidelines includes a director of
Queens Moat Houses, the heavily indebted hotel chain that commissioned two
valuations last year from two different firms which came in nearly Pounds
500m apart. Who else sat on or advised the committee? Representatives from
both those firms: Jones Lang Wootton and Weatherall Green &amp; Smith.
